===Etymology 3===
From [[onomatopoeic]] {{term|はた|tr=hata|lang=ja}}, possibly for the sound of the shuttle running back and forth, or for the sound of a woven cloth moving in the wind, compare {{term|旗||a flag|tr=hata|lang=ja}}.

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|はた}}

# a [[loom]]
# [[woven]] [[cloth]]

===Etymology 4===
Stem form ({{term|連用形|lang=ja}}) of the verb {{term|機る||to [[manipulate]] something|tr=wakatsuru|lang=ja}}, itself an alteration of {{term|誘る||to [[manipulate]] or [[con]] someone|tr=okotsuru|lang=ja}}, a compound of {{term|痴||a fool|tr=oko|lang=ja}} + {{term|釣る||to [[fish]], to [[draw out]]|tr=tsuru|lang=ja}}.

# to [[manipulate]] {{qualifier|as in a device}}
# to [[manipulate]] {{qualifier|as in a person}}: to [[deceive]], to [[take in]] someone
# to get on someone's right side; to [[humor]] someone; to [[make an effort]] to [[please]] someone

